---
interface Props {
  copy: {
    eyebrow: string
    timestamp: string
  }
  panel: {
    humidity: number
  }
}

const { copy, panel } = Astro.props
---

<style>
  @keyframes pulse-dot {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50%       { opacity: 0.3; }
  }
  .pulse-dot {
    animation: pulse-dot 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
</style>

<section
  class="px-6 py-7"
  style="background:#F1E8D9;"
>
  <div class="max-w-hub mx-auto">

    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
      <span
        class="pulse-dot inline-block flex-shrink-0"
        style="width:7px;height:7px;background:#A2384B;border-radius:50%;"
        aria-hidden="true"
      ></span>
      <p class="font-sans text-ink uppercase" style="font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.10em;">
        {copy.eyebrow}
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="font-sans text-taupe mb-3" style="font-size:12px;">
      {copy.timestamp}
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-ink max-w-prose"
      style="font-family:'Newsreader',Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;"
    >
      Indoor relative humidity across the UK is sitting around{' '}
      <strong style="font-size:18px;font-style:italic;">{panel.humidity}%</strong>
      {' '}right now — well below the threshold where glycerin-based products start working with your hair instead of against it. If your wash-and-go has been reverting faster than usual, or your ends feel papery by day two, this is probably why.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>
